sentences.sentence:
Order 35A r 3(2)(c) provides as follows:
 If a respondent is in default, the Court may: ... (c) if the proceeding was commenced by an application supported by a statement of claim or the Court has ordered that the proceeding continue on pleadings - give judgment against the respondent for the relief that: (i) the applicant appears entitled to on the statement of claim; and (ii) the Court is satisfied it has power to grant; 
2 The proceedings were commenced by an application on 9 April 2008.
